results.full_model_response:
<think> 
Computed the discriminant: D = 97² - 4*(-7)*(-31) = 9409 - 868 = 8541. Then used the quadratic formula: n = (97 ± √8541) / (2×-7). Multiplying the equation by -1 yields 7n² - 97n + 31 = 0, so n = (97 ± √8541)/(14). Approximating √8541 ≈ 92.42 gives the solutions: n ≈ (97 - 92.42)/14 ≈ 0.3271 and n ≈ (97 + 92.42)/14 ≈ 13.5300.
